    "11 LeGendre et al. (2022) accomplishes this by investigating a set of pre-correction (kernel) matrices applied to inner and outer LED wall frustums.",
    "Then with a separate post-correction matrix applied to the in-camera image, pixels are re-maped to the desired/expected color schema.",
    "The pre-correction matrices are solved by comparing and minimizing the difference between the expected LED emission spectral sensitivity functions and the resulting sensitivity function captured by the camera.",
    "This optimization is accomplished for a given color chart.",
    "7 Testing on a variety of color charts showed near-optimal results, though resulting errors are limited by the size of the pre-and post-correction kernels."
